3c/div\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eArea (sqm)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e430\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003eCompleted\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e2023\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e      \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n              \n      \n              \u003cp\u003eNestled in the countryside of Pudong on the outskirts of Shanghai, this six-bedroom holiday house was conceived as a retreat for an extended family seeking to reconnect with nature and spend quality time together. Shanghai-based architectural office \u003ca href=\"http://www.atelierli.cn/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAtelier LI\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e has seamlessly integrated modern architectural elements with traditional design principles, all within the constraints of local building regulations, \u003cstrong\u003eto bridge two worlds: the traditional lifestyle of the elderly residents, who continue their farming practices, and the contemporary urban lifestyle of the younger generation, who enjoy modern comforts while enjoying the serene landscape\u003c/strong\u003e. The result is a new typology for country houses in China—one that harmonizes modern aesthetics, practicality, and cultural relevance while fostering an ongoing dialogue between tradition and innovation.\u003c/p\u003e\n          \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/02_pudong_villa_atelier_li_wm_studio_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/02_pudong_villa_atelier_li_wm_studio_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" alt=\"Photography © WM STUDIO.\" title=\"Photography © WM STUDIO.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/file